underlying_goal: Resolve complex merge conflicts in an Xcode project, then disable auto-updates and notifications.
friction_detail: The build process failed on the first attempt due to network issues while resolving Swift Package Manager dependencies, requiring a retry.
primary_success: Successfully resolved five complex merge conflicts in a Swift codebase by logically integrating changes from both branches, such as keeping a local configuration setting while adopting an upstream refactoring of service initializers. The final code compiled successfully.
brief_summary: The user needed to merge an upstream branch, resulting in five conflicting Swift files. Claude systematically resolved each conflict, preserving local intent while adopting upstream architectural changes. After a successful build, Claude then implemented the user's request to disable auto-updates and notifications, committing and pushing both sets of changes.
